            "id": "4530705",
            "title": "Epsilon Energy divests Dewey Energy Holdings and assets in Anadarko basin",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Epsilon Energy (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EPSN\" title=\"Epsilon Energy Ltd.\">EPSN</a></span>) on Thursday announced the divestment of its wholly owned subsidiary, Dewey Energy Holdings, which holds the company’s <span class=\"location\">Western Anadarko</span> basin assets, to an undisclosed private buyer.</li>\n<li>The assets sold included about 813 Mcfe/d (60% natural gas) of production (Q3 2025 figure) and approximately 6,400 net deep acres and 2,200 net shallow acres of leasehold, all located in <span class=\"location\">Dewey County, Oklahoma, the company said.</span>\n</li>\n<li>The purchase price was $2.5 million in cash.</li>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20337527-epsilon-energy-ltd-announces-the-divestment-of-dewey-energy-holdings-llc-and-the-company-s\">Press Release</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
