            "id": "4530692",
            "title": "T-Mobile authorizes new shareholder return program of up to $14.6B",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">T-Mobile US (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TMUS\" title=\"T-Mobile US, Inc.\">TMUS</a></span>) announced a new shareholder return program of up to $14.6 billion that is expected to consist of additional repurchases of shares of the company’s common stock, and payment of cash dividends.</p>\n<p>The telecom giant said the program will run through December 31, 2026.</p>\n<p>According to a <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/filings/pdf/18990763\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"filing\">filing</a>, the amount available under the shareholder return program for share repurchases will be reduced by the amount of any cash dividends declared and paid by the company, including the first quarter cash <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4528774-t-mobile-us-declares-1_02-dividend\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"dividend \">dividend </a>of $1.02 per share payable on March 12, 2026.</p>\n<p>The shareholder return program is in addition to the company’s $14 billion shareholder return program announced in December 2024 that runs through December 31, 2025, T-Mobile said, adding that any remaining unusedamount under the 2025 program shall be added to the 2026 program.</p>\n<p>The company expects that the share repurchases and any dividends declared and paid to be made from available cash on hand andproceeds of one or more debt issuances or other borrowings.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
